at no matter what, he wouldn\x{2019}t look Derek in the eye for the whole practice, so that he didn\x{2019}t get the wrong idea.They were sitting on the bench one Friday afternoon, watching everyone else play Rivendell. Sterling was expected to be able to kick their collective ass with their eyes closed (not that that was reason enough for the coach to put Peter or Derek in to actually play during a real league game). The score was climbing to something humiliating in the last minute of the final quarter-Sterling 24, Rivendell 2-and Derek was telling Peter another joke.\x{201c}A pirate walks into a bar with a parrot on his shoulder, a peg leg, and a steering wheel on his pants,\x{201d} Derek said. \x{201c}The bartender says, \x{2018}Hey, you\x{2019}ve got a steering wheel on your pants.\x{2019} And the pirate goes, \x{2018}Arrrgh, I know. It\x{2019}s driving me nuts.\x{2019}\x{201d}\x{201c}Good game,\x{201d} the coach said, congratulating each of the players with a handshake. \x{201c}Good game. Good game.\x{201d}\x{201c}You coming?\x{201d} Derek asked, standing up.\x{201c}I\x{2019}ll meet you in there,\x{201d} Peter said, and as he leaned down to retie his cleats he saw a pair of lady\x{2019}s shoes stop in front of him-a pair he recognized, because he was always tripping over them in the mudroom.\x{201c}Hi, baby,\x{201d} his mother said, smiling down.Peter choked. What middle school kid had Mommy come to pick him up right at the field, as if he were leaving nursery school and needed a hand crossing the street?\x{201c}Just give me a second, Peter,\x{201d} his mother said.He glanced up long enough to see that the team had not gone into the locker room, as usual, but hung around to watch this latest humiliation. Just when he thought it couldn\x{2019}t get any worse, his mother marched up to the coach. \x{201c}Coach Yarbrowski,\x{201d} she said. \x{201c}Could I have a word?\x{201d}Kill me now, Peter thought.\x{201c}I\x{2019}m Peter\x{2019}s mother. And I\x{2019}m wonde