otion Alex didn\x{2019}t even have words for-the animal instinct that came when you realized someone you love has been taken hostage.McAfee had committed the grievous sin of dragging Josie into this, and Alex\x{2019}s mind spiraled wildly as she wondered what she could do to get him fired, or even disbarred. Come to think of it, she didn\x{2019}t even really care if retribution came within the confines of the law or outside it. But suddenly, Alex stilled. It wasn\x{2019}t Jordan McAfee she\x{2019}d chase to the ends of the earth-it was Josie. She\x{2019}d do anything to keep her daughter from being hurt again.Maybe she should thank Jordan McAfee for making her realize that she already had the raw material in her to be a good mother, after all.Alex sat down at her laptop and began to type. Her heart was hammering as she walked out to the clerk\x{2019}s desk and handed the sheet of paper to Eleanor; but that was normal, wasn\x{2019}t it, when you were about to leap off a cliff?\x{201c}You need to call Judge Wagner,\x{201d} Alex said.It wasn\x{2019}t Patrick who needed the search warrant. But when he heard another officer talking about swinging by the courthouse, he interceded. \x{201c}I\x{2019}m headed out that way,\x{201d} he\x{2019}d said. \x{201c}I\x{2019}ll do it for you.\x{201d}In truth, he hadn\x{2019}t been heading toward the courthouse, at least not until he\x{2019}d volunteered. And he wasn\x{2019}t such a Samaritan that he\x{2019}d drive forty miles out of the goodness of his heart. Patrick wanted to go there for one reason only: it was another excuse to see Alex Cormier.He pulled into an empty spot and got out of his car, immediately spotting her Honda. This was a good thing; for all he knew, she might not even have been in court today. But then he did a double take as he realized that someone was in the car\x{2026}and that that someone was the judge.She wasn\x{2019}t moving, just staring out the windshield. The wipers were on, but it wasn\x{2019}t raining. It looked like she didn\x{2019}t even realize she was crying.He felt that same uneasy sway in the pit of his stomach that usually came when he\x{2019}d reached a crime scene and saw a victim\x{2019}s tears. I\x{2019}m too late, he thought. Again.Patrick approached the car, but the judge must not have seen him coming. When he knocked on the window, she jumped a foot and hurriedly wiped her eyes. He mimed for her to roll down the window. \x{201c}Everything okay?\x{201d} he asked.\x{201c}I\x{2019}m fine.\x{201d}\x{201c}You don\x{2019}t look fine.\x{201d}\x{201c}Then stop looking,\x{201d} she snapped.He hooked his fingers over the curl of the car door. \x{201c}Listen. You want to go somewhere and talk? I\x{2019}ll buy you coffee.\x{201d}The judge sighed. \x{201c}You can\x{2019}t buy me coffee.\x{201d}\x{201c}Well, we can still get some.\x{201d} He stood up and walked around to the passenger door, opened it, slid into the seat beside her.\x{201c}You\x{2019}re on duty,\x{201d} she pointed out.\x{201c}I\x{2019}m taking my lunch break.\x{201d}\x{201c}At <<ten in the morning|5>>?\x{201d}He reached across the console to the keys, dangling in the ignition, and started the car. \x{201c}Head out of the parking lot and take a left, all right?\x{201d}\x{201c}Or what?\x{201d}\x{201c}For God\x{2019}s sake, don\x{2019}t you know better than to argue with someone who\x{2019}s wearing a Glock?\x{201d}She looked at him for a long moment. \x{201c}You couldn\x{2019}t possibly be carjacking me,\x{201d} the judge said, but she started driving, as he\x{2019}d asked.\x{201c}Remind me to arrest myself later,\x{201d} Patrick said.Alex had been raised by her father to give everything her best shot, and apparently, that included falling off the deep end. Why not recuse herself from the biggest trial of her career, ask for administrative leave, and go out for coffee with the detective on the case all in one fell swoop?Then again, she told herself, if she hadn\x{2019}t gone out with Patrick Ducharme, she would never have known that the Golden Dragon Chinese restaurant opened for business at <<10:00 a.m.|2a>>If she hadn\x{2019}t gone out with him, she would have had to drive home and start her life over.Everyone at the restaurant seemed to know the detective and didn\x{2019}t mind him going into the kitchen to get Alex her cup of coffee. \x{201c}What you saw back there,\x{201d} Alex said hesitantly. \x{201c}You won\x{2019}t\x{2026}\x{201d}\x{201c}Tell anyone you were having a little breakdown in your car?\x{201d}She looked down at the mug he set in front of her, not even really knowing how to respond. In her experience, the moment you showed you were weak in front of someone, they\x{2019}d use it against you. \x{201c}It\x{2019}s hard to be a judge sometimes. People expect you to act like one, even when you\x{2019}ve got the flu and feel like crawling up into a ball and dying, or cursing out the cashier who shortchanged you on purpose. There\x{2019}s not a lot of room for mistakes.\x{201d}\x{201c}Your secret\x{2019}s safe,\x{201d} Patrick said. \x{201c}I won\x{2019}t tell anyone in the law enforcement community that you\x{2019}ve actually got emotions.\x{201d}Alex took a sip of the coffee, then looked up at him. \x{201c}Sugar?\x{201d}Patrick folded his arms on the bar and leaned toward her. \x{201c}Darling?\x{201d} At her expression, he started to laugh, and then handed her the bowl. \x{201c}Honestly, it\x{2019}s no big deal. We all have lousy days at work.\x{201d}\x{201c}Do you sit in your car and cry?\x{201d}\x{201c}Not recently, but I have been known to overturn evidence lockers during fits of frustration.\x{201d} He poured milk into a creamer and set it down. \x{201c}You know, it\x{2019}s not mutually exclusive.\x{201d}\x{201c}What\x{2019}s not?\x{201d}\x{201c}Being a judge and being human.\x{201d}Alex added the milk to her mug. \x{201c}Tell that to everyone who wants me to recuse myself.\x{201d}\x{201c}Isn\x{2019}t this the part where you tell me we can\x