ffs were firmly holding her back.Wagner was smacking his gavel, although nobody gave a damn. \x{201c}We\x{2019}ll take a fifteen-minute recess,\x{201d} he ordered, and as another bailiff hauled Peter through a rear door, the judge turned to Josie. \x{201c}Young lady,\x{201d} he said, \x{201c}you are still under oath.\x{201d}Alex watched Josie being taken through another door, and she called out after her. A moment later, Eleanor was at her side. The clerk took Alex\x{2019}s arm. \x{201c}Judge, come with me. You\x{2019}re not safe out here right now.\x{201d}For the first time she could actively remember, Alex allowed herself to be led.Patrick arrived in the courtroom just as it exploded. He saw Josie on the stand, crying desperately; he saw Judge Wagner fighting for control-but most of all, he saw Alex single-mindedly trying to get to her daughter.He would have drawn his gun right then and there to help her do it.By the time he fought his way down the central aisle of the courtroom, Alex was gone. He caught a glimpse of her as she slipped into a room behind the bench, and he hurdled the bar to follow her but felt someone grab his sleeve. Annoyed, he glanced down to see Diana Leven.\x{201c}What the hell is going on?\x{201d} he asked.\x{201c}You first.\x{201d}He sighed. \x{201c}I spent the night at Sterling High, trying to check Josie\x{2019}s statement. It didn\x{2019}t make sense-if Matt had fired at Peter, there should have been physical evidence of destruction in the wall behind him. I assumed that she was lying again-that Peter had been the one to shoot Matt unprovoked. Once I figured out where that first bullet hit, I used a laser to see where it could have ricocheted-and then I understood why we didn\x{2019}t find it the first time around.\x{201d} Digging in his coat, he extracted an evidence bag with a slug inside. \x{201c}The fire department helped me dig it out of a maple tree outside the window in the shower stall. I drove it straight to the lab for testing-